essuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aPopulations around the globe are ageing rapidly. This demographic shift affects families, market structures and social provisions. This timely volume, part of the Ageing and the Lifecourse series, argues that the lifecourse perspective helps us understand the causes and effects of population ageing. The lifecourse perspective suggests that individuals’ experiences at an early age can influence their decisions and behaviour at a later age. This much-needed volume combines insights from different disciplines and real-life experiences to describe the theories and practices behind this idea. It therefore caters to the needs of scholars, practitioners and policy makers in a range of areas including sociology and political science.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAging. 0aDemography. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gerontology.2bisacsh1 aAboim, Sofia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, J. Scott, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCong, Zhen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFranke, Annette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaapola, Ilkka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohansson, Stina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohansson, Stina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKaristo, Antti, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeene, Jennifer R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKomp, Kathrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKomp, Kathrin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLarsson, 